      "source_location": "Section on compressive strength",
      "evidence_text": ", respectively. Subsequently, with prolonged water curing period of 28 days, the POFA–HSGCs exhibit greater strength than the OPC concrete, with strength value of 91.4, 98.3, 104.2, and 98.1 MPa for OPC, POFA20, POFA40 and POFA60, respec- tively with the POFA40 exhibiting the highest 28 days strength. Hence, all of the POFA–HSGC mixes achieve greater strength than the OPC concrete at 28 days, with an increase of 7.5%, 14% and 7.3% for POFA20, POFA40 and POFA60, respectively. This could be attributed to the pozzolanic reaction between the POFA and Ca(OH)2, to produce secondary calcium–silicate–hydrate (C–S–H), densifying the concrete microstructure, res",
